data.description: ACCEPTIN BACK UPS.Welcome home to this updated Mediterranean oasis on a very private street. This beauty is located in the Westwinds community of Tarpon Springs where there is 54 homes on a single winding drive. No rear neighbors, and because it's the last home on the street, there's no traffic in the front. Location is great withing walking distance to all schools and local beaches/parks. Enter through double doors into the living/dining room area with high ceilings and beautiful Romano Travertine floors. The master suite is off to the right, it is spacious and has sliders out to the pool. The en suite bathroom will delight you with the double sink vanity and large walk in shower and closet. On the other side of the house is the other two bedrooms which share a bathroom and offer privacy from the master suite. The kitchen is light and bright with granite counters and stainless steel appliances. The family room is next to the kitchen so the cook can enjoy in the family fun and conversations while cooking, The fireplace is wood burning and adds a coziness to the room. There is also a dinette off the kitchen. They all overlook the 27X27 lanai, sparkling pool and lush landscaping through sliders. Other amenities include a sealed terracotta roof, plantation shutters, neural color paint scheme, gutter and downspouts, a paver walking path around the house and a sprinkler system that uses reclaimed water.(lower water bill) Enjoy the easy cleaning with hard surface floors through out the house. MOVE IN READY! Location is excellent. Minutes away from top ranked schools, beaches, restaurants, shopping, historic downtown Tarpon Springs, Pinellas Trail, and the famous Sponge Docks. Don't miss out on this beauty!!
